Surgical treatment of mediastinal cysts: report on 29 cases. Mediastinal cysts are rare, forming 12-18% of all primary mediastinal tumors. The purpose of this study is to evaluate type, clinical properties, treatment modalities, and results of mediastinal cystic neoplasm in the light of available literature.We retrospectively investigated 29 patients who were diagnosed and surgically treated for mediastinal cysts in our clinic between January 1996 and May 2011.Sixteen (55.2%) patients were male and 13 (44.8%) were female. The average age of the patients was 36.5 +/- 22.1 (17-77 years old). The mediastinal cysts comprised 11 (37.9%) bronchogenic cysts seven (24.1%) hydatid cystsA surgical approach to mediastinal cysts offers histological analysis, pathological diagnosis, curative treatment, and prevention from complications.